# Simple 2D Game Engine
#
# A Simple-native 2D game engine with:
# - Scene graph (Node2D hierarchy)
# - Component system (composition-based)
# - Software renderer (primitive render commands on a CPU pixel buffer)
# - Interpreter-backed 2D physics runtime for the current demo path
# - Input (interpreter-backed winit keyboard/mouse path)
# - Audio (explicit silent backend until host audio runtime exists)
#
# Modules:
# - resource: Handle-based resource management
# - scene: Scene graph (Node2D, SceneTree)
# - component: Component system
# - render: 2D renderer
# - sprite: Texture and sprite assets
# - physics: 2D physics (Rapier2D wrapper)
# - input: Input system (action mapping)
# - audio: Audio system (bus-based)
# - core: Game loop, time, Engine2D
